@startuml
title Object Diagram for UpdateItemCommand Feature
hide circle
left to right direction

object "<u>updateParser:UpdateCommandParser</u>" as parser
object "<u>cmd:UpdateItemCommand</u>" as command {
  categoryName = "fruits"
  itemIndex = 1
  updates = {qty=20, expiryDate=2026-4-15}
}
object "<u>inventory:Inventory</u>" as inventory
object "<u>fruits:Category</u>" as fruits {
  name = "fruits"
}
object "<u>snacks:Category</u>" as snacks {
  name = "snacks"
}
object "<u>apple:Item</u>" as apple {
  name = "apple"
  quantity = 20
  binLocation = "A-1"
  expiryDate = "2026-4-15"
}
object "<u>chips:Item</u>" as chips {
  name = "chips"
  quantity = 8
  binLocation = "B-2"
  expiryDate = "2026-5-01"
}
object "<u>fieldParser:CommonFieldParser</u>" as fieldParser
object "<u>duplicateParser:DuplicateIdentityParser</u>" as duplicateParser
object "<u>:UI</u>" as ui

note as N1
  This snapshot shows one execution after the
  first fruits item has been updated.
  The command targets item index 1 and applies
  two field changes through the shared update map.
  During duplicate checking, command directly calls
  duplicateParser.findDuplicateItem(fruits, apple).
end note

parser --> command : creates >
command --> inventory : queries >
command --> fruits : targets >
command --> apple : updates >
command --> fieldParser : validates with >
command --> duplicateParser : checks duplicates via >
command --> ui : shows result via >
inventory --> fruits : contains >
inventory --> snacks : contains >
fruits --> apple : contains >
snacks --> chips : contains >
@enduml
